File: mochi.info,  Node: Function mod_impulse m op_point t_end [opts],  Next: Function mod_cascade SS1 SS2,  Prev: Function mod_step m op_point t_end [opts],  Up: Definitions for mochi

 -- Function: mod_impulse (M, OP_POINT, T_END, [OPTS])
     Convenience wrappers over ‘mod_simulate’:

        • ‘mod_step’ applies a step to the chosen input (‘input_index’,
          default 1) of magnitude ‘magnitude’ (default 1), with all
          other inputs held at zero.
        • ‘mod_impulse’ applies a discrete impulse approximation: ‘u[0]
          = magnitude/dt’ on the chosen input, zero thereafter, so that
          ∫u dt ≈ magnitude.

     Both accept the same opts as ‘mod_simulate’ plus ‘input_index’ and
     ‘magnitude’.


